narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: If you want to advance your Japanese (particularly reading and writing), this is the class for you!
If you took J150, why stop there? :) If you've tested straight into J151, be sure you get a feel for the rhythm of the classroom, which is pretty idiosyncratic.

A continuation of JAPN150, similar in style and the kind of content covered, workload remains largely the same also. The content ranges from historical to contemporary topics, especially culture in Japan that everyone knows about but no one really knows about in detail which is really informative for a more profound of the culture of the language that you will be studying.
